  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Phase-out of HCFC-22 and HCFC-141b at Al Hafez Group</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Phase-out of HCFC-22 and HCFC-141b from the manufacture of unitary air-conditioning equipment and rigid PU insulation panels at Al Hafez Group  HCFC-22 and HCFC-141b used in the manufacture of unitary air-conditioners and ice plants at Al Hafez group plants in Syria  will be phased out by converting to HFC refrigeration technology and aqueous cleaning technology.   HCFC-141b used for the manufacture of rigid PU panels will also be phased out by converting to cyclopentane foam blowing technology.  Implementation of this project will contribute to Syria being in compliance with the 2013 and 2015 targets under the Montreal Protocol (HCFC baseline freeze and 10% reduction respectively).</narrative>
  </description>
